column2: Ramadiyya is the offshoot of Pusaka that combined Mahayana monkhood, Cham tribalism and Sunni theology together. Their followers believe in the concept of Dhammaraja and that if their King is pious enough, he could lead his people to pure land where no suffering shall befall them. Their ultimate goal is to spread the word of Prophet Madiyyah and Muhammad and prepare the staging ground for Rama-Buddha's Pure Land.
